column4: Toys - Baby and Toddler Toys - Learning & Activity Toys - Sound and Light Activity Toys
column73:
The Toddler Jams musical toy by Baby Einstein lets baby move and groove to 30+ melodies. Introduce a world of music with selections ranging from classical songs to pop music to global genres. This take along toy has an easy-to-grab handle for a concert on the go. A colorful light show plays along to the beat of the music, encouraging development of fine motor skills as baby dances to the rhythm. With bright buttons, he can pause, skip, replay or re-mix it up. This music player is a toddler toy that sparks a lifelong love of music.

Size: 12 x 6 x 22 cm

Race out in wild action with Batmobile RC in 1:20 scale. The remote-controlled Batmobile has a remote control that is easy to control. With authentic The Batman movie styling and incredible details that bring your Batmobile to life. The 2.4 GHz dual joystick remote is USB rechargeable and has out-of-range sensors, so you know when your Batmobile should stay within range, recharge and be ready for action again. True Batman fans will love this Batmobile and its detailed decoration and sculpture, as seen in The Batman Movie, making it a great gift idea for Batman fans. DC fans of all ages love this Batmobile collectible, toy characters and play set to engage their imagination and create their own epic Batman missions. Protect Gotham City with your Batmobile RC vehicle. From 4 years. Batteries (3xAAA). excl + Batteries (2xAAA). excl.

column4: Toys - Dolls and Dollhouses - Dolls & Accessories - Dolls Feeding Kit
column73:
Baby Annabell already eats purée. But we haven’t yet figured out which kind she really likes. The pink chair with its lamb backrest and table can help with that.

Time for the main course. Carrot or pea purée or rice porridge? When the bowl is placed on the relevant sheep, light and sound indicate whether or not Baby Annabell likes her lunch. If the field lights up green, the little doll murmurs happily and eagerly waits for the next spoonful. If it lights up red, try giving her another dish, otherwise Baby Annabell will protest with a loud “Yuck!”. For dessert
